4. Calculating and adding interest
:SKRSLUT
:SWISS8.
.sp 3mm
This section does not apply to your payment accounts - please see
'Addendum on payment services'.
.sp 3mm
A payment account is an account set up for the purpose of executing
payment transactions. Examples of payment accounts are your salary and
budget accounts.
.sp 3mm
A working day is a day when the payer's or the payee's relevant
provider which is involved in the execution of a payment transaction
is open as is required to execute a payment
transaction. Saturdays, Sundays, public holidays, Constitution
Day (5 June), Friday after Ascension Day, Christmas Eve and New Year's
Eve are non-working days at &BANKNAVN..
.sp 3mm
Every day, &BANKNAVN. calculates interest for each account as follows:
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Balance x nominal interest/360.
.sp 3mm
All months are calculated as 30 days.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When determining the daily balance, &BANKNAVN. uses the interest date for
the transactions as a basis.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The interest date is the day on which a payment, disbursement or other
transaction affects the calculation of interest on an account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Generally, the following rules apply:
.sp 3mm
When you make a payment in cash, by cheque or Dankort into an account at
&BANKNAVN., the interest date is (the first working day/working day after
the payment is made).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When cash is paid out to you on a cheque issued to you, the interest
date is (the working day/first working day after the disbursement is
made). The interest date for payment of this cheque into your account at
&BANKNAVN. is (the first working day after the payment is made/payment
date).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When cash or a cheque is paid out to you from your account at
&BANKNAVN., the interest date is (the working day/first working day
after the disbursement date).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When you transfer money between your own accounts at &BANKNAVN., the
interest date for both accounts is (the working day/first working day
after the transfer).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When wages, public benefits etc. are paid to you, the interest date is
(the first working day after the book date/availability date).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When you receive other transfers from an account in a Danish bank, the
interest date is (the first working day after the transfer is received
and booked/transfer date).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
.us Adding interest
.br
&BANKNAVN. adds interest on
.us deposits
.ct  once a year. This is done by
adding the daily interest calculations and depositing the total amount
into your account. The interest date is (the day interest is
added/first working day after interest is added).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. adds interest on
.us loans
.ct  either monthly, quarterly or semi-annually. The interest-paying
period is stated on the loan application.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Interest is added by adding the daily interest calculations and
withdrawing the total amount from your account. The interest date is
(the day interest is added/first working day after interest is added).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The interest added is stated in your passbook and on your account
statements or similar statements.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. may decide that interest amounts below a certain limit are
not added to the account.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
