7.  Payments and withdrawals
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
.us Reservations - deposits
.br
All payments into your account which are not made in cash are subject
to &BANKNAVN. receiving the payment. The same applies to payments made
by cheque drawn on accounts at &BANKNAVN.. The reservation applies even
if not mentioned on your receipt or in another deposit notice.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If a cheque, for example, bounces, &BANKNAVN. will withdraw the amount
from your account again. &BANKNAVN. will notify you if a withdrawal is
made from your account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. may reverse amounts deposited into your account by obvious
mistake on the part of &BANKNAVN., for example if the same amount is
deposited twice.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
.us Using payments
.br
Any payment on a loan or credit is first used to cover interest and
commission payments. This applies whether the payment is made by you or
a guarantor or pledger.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Remaining payments will be used to cover instalments.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
.us Adjusting payment
.br
&BANKNAVN. is entitled, but not obliged to increase the payment to meet
increasing interest levels, commission or similar.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
.us Printouts
.br
When receiving paper or electronic account statements, you should
promptly check if there have been any unauthorised transactions in your
account. If this is the case, you must contact &BANKNAVN. immediately.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
A transcript of &BANKNAVN.'s registers will always be deemed valid
proof of the outstanding balance.
